---
description: Trading decision agent workflow for this repository
alwaysApply: true
---

Use `AGENTS.md` as the source of truth.

The user should be able to talk naturally. Internally call `python -m trading_agent.cli ...` to route requests, inspect memory, fetch quote evidence, and generate skill packets. When the user clearly reports factual buy/sell/add/reduce/clear changes, follow `skills/memory_update.md` and **edit** `memory/portfolio.md` / `memory/watchlist.md` directly (the CLI does not auto-write memory). Do not treat questions or plans like “能不能买/是否加仓/准备买入/要不要卖” as completed trade updates.

For A-share analysis, if the user gives only a Chinese stock name, first resolve it yourself to the 6-digit code before calling the CLI quote/judgment commands. Reuse existing same-symbol quote evidence in the current conversation when the market and window are unchanged; do not refetch the same quote data unnecessarily.

Normal new-position buy judgments can continue with an empty portfolio. Explicit add-buy, sell judgments, and next-day plans require complete holding information first.

Do not ask the user to run commands unless they ask how to test the project.
